rComments: Unclear grading, posted everyone's grades for the whole class to see. Large portion of students dropped the course. Pretty sure she deducted marks for a missed class due to COVID. Will alter your artwork without your permission.

This was my first experience with sculpture and it was pretty hard. For almost every week, you need to spend at least 4 or more hours to complete your sculpture homework. In some cases, you may spend 12 hours to complete a thing. Although I did everything needed and noted everything (she checks notebooks), I got a C+. I'm happy that it's finished.

Carla laughed at me, insulted me and my classmates and broke my sculpture at one point without asking me because it "wasn't dynamic enough". She yelled at me when I asked for clarification and belittled me in front of the class on a few occasions. would not recommend.

This professor is by far one of the best one will ever experience. If you are hard working and devoted to your studies, this professor is one for you. You will learn to develop your work through a variety of thought provoking projects and most importantly, learn to articulate what you see. This professor will help any art student to grow.

Had Carla in sculpture and drawing. She is very educated in both subjects and is committed to teaching. I learnt SO MUCH with her. If you ignore her odd, sometimes inappropriate comments and focus on her teaching of techniques you will do good in the class. You need to be focused and ready to work and learn. She is tough but one of my fav profs.
By far the worst prof I have ever had. Do anything you can to make sure you do not get her. She is very disrespectful of her students and does not appreciate them at all.

She has no respect for her students work. I had her in sculpture and would recommend avoiding her at all cost. If you can choose between her and another teacher, choose the other teacher! Her assignment are so vague, it seems like she plans the course week to week without really thinking about it. She never helps, only yells.
She is the Prof I enjoyed the least.
She is very understanding and helpful when asked. very passionate about her subject. DO NOT SKIP CLASS THOUGH.

hours of hard work to sort out confusing instructions, contradictory instructions and got disrespectful, offhand feed back... Yet I have been rated as having "excellent drawing skills" from the OSA programs director ... on the SAME  pictures!

Carla est une prof très exigente envers ses étudiants autant en sculpture qu'en peinture. Elle nous fait apprendre tellement et nous pousse plus loin. Je peux dire sans aucun doute qu'elle a été ma meilleure prof dans le département. Ses cours prennent beaucoup de temps en dehors des ateliers.

I only had Carla in one class in my last year and she was amazing! She is one of those ladies who won't let people get away with murder. If you respect her she will respect you back. She is definitely one of the most compassionate, motivational and helpful professors on staff.

Second year Drawing: She's very difficult, but in all, she pushes you and pushes you and you learn SO MUCH. I mean, SO MUCH. If you aren't challenged or pushed, you don't improve. So if you want a wishy washy class, don't take this class. But if you want someone who KNOWS what she's doing and can teach you, take this class.
Even though I wasn't one of her favourites and she appears to flirt with the younger men sometimes, I thought she was alright.

It's all about process with the "dragon". She will shake up your artistic practice, but ultimately, you will be better for it. Be prepared to abandon figuration while you  learn a new appreciation for abstraction. If Carla doesn't break you, she'll make you stronger. A challenge.

I really enjoyed this prof, i had her for my first year sculpture class. I found her attitude refreshing and liked how she pushed her students. i enjoyed the assignments and found the critiques to be helpful. i also liked her as a person. if you are a wimp or a slacker, watch out. i would gladly take a class with her again.
terrible, terrible class as a result of the prof. Do ANYTHING within your power to avoid her. She isn't as important as she makes herself out to be.

Instructions are very abstract and cryptic...difficult to pin down exactly what is expected of you, and generally results in student feeling inadequate and utterly un-artistic.  Her passion for art is inspiring, however and she becomes less scary and almost likeable by the end of term.

The fact that she graduated from OttawaU says something about her understanding of what art is. Apparently hundreds of years of successful drawing teaching no longer applies in today's world. Scribbles are the way to go...    wow.
this is the only drawing professor i have ever hated, sure, i did benefit from the challenge, but she was very confusing as well as (shall i be blunt?) a bag. and i did get an A. so there.

Her approach is "If you show signs of already being a promising artist, I'll give you time, if I don't think you're good, I'll tell you that you 'just don't got it' near the end of the year without having done anything to teach you anything or improv
She can be very intense, almost overbearing. If she doesn't like something, she'll say so...which is often. Scares me a little.
definitely not a people person. doesn't seem willing to help you and is almost condescending when you don't understand. can make you feel stupid and insignificant during critiques.
